<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-370-316  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 370 316.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  June 19 1989 v6 n24 p21(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Real-time text manager accesses wire services. (Verity's Topic2.0) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ballou, Melinda-Carol.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Verity Inc introduces the Topic 2.0 data base management software.andO;The $2,500 Topic 2.0 supports real-time information sources suchas wire services and automatically routes information on subjectthat is of particular interest to the user.andP;  The real-timecapability can be used to filter information from the barrage ofelectronic junk mail received by the user.andP;  The software'sHyperLinks feature enables users to cross-reference information bycreating links between related documents and other information.andO;The Topic Image Filters feature allows user to retrieve images ofdiffering formats, such as PC-X, Sun and PDA formats.andP;  Users canautomatically generate queries through the Topic-By-Examplefeature.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Verity Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Topic 2.0 (Data base management system) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionData Base Management SystemsSoftware PackagesReal-Time Systemsautomatic message handlers.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Real-Time Text Manager Accesses Wire ServicesandM;MOUNTAIN VIEW, Calif.andP;  -- Verity has released version 2.0 of Topic, thecompany's text information management system, that supports real-timeinformation sources such as wire services via &quot;Topic Real Time&quot; as well ashypertext capabilities for images.andM;Verity also announced volume shipments of the Topic SQL-Bridge, an interfacebetween Topic and SQL relational database products from Oracle, RelationalTechnology, Sybase and Informix.andM;&quot;Topic's support for real-time information sources will automatically routeinformation to you if you're interested in a certain suject,&quot; said RobertWilliams, Verity's vice president of marketing.andM;&quot;this is especially useful for brokers and investors, for instance, who musthave information as quickly as possible to maintain a competitive edge,&quot; hesaid.andP;  &quot;Or the real-time capability can be used for E-mail.andP;  People arebombarded by electronic garbage mail.andP;  Topic lets you filter information fromthe junk mail you may be receiving.&quot;andM;Topic's new HyperLinks feature allows users to cross-reference information byproviding links between related documents and other information, companyofficials explained.andM;The HyperLinks can consist of &quot;sticky notes&quot; or annotations that have beenclipped onto the documents, illustrations and other graphics images orrelated documents not retrieved by a Topic search, the officials said.andP;  Iconsindicate the presence of HyperLinks, which, when the user selects them,display the information associated with the link.andM;Image Retrieval, TooandM;Through another new capability, Topic Image Filters, users can retrieveimages of differing formats, such as TIFF (Tagged Image File Format), PC-X,Sun, raster and PDA formats.andP;  Users can also compress images, conforming toCCITT level 3 and 4 standards, the officials said.andM;In addition, version 2.0 includes a Topic-By-Example feature, which enablesusers to automatically generate queries, and an application programminginterface (API) for third-party developers.andM;The Topic API that is available with version 2.0 is a library of C functionsthat allow third-party developers to embed Topic, with its text search andretrieval capabilities, into their applications.andM;&quot;We hope to encourage third parties who need these kinds of capabilities toincorporate Topic into their software,&quot; Williams elaborated.andM;With the Topic SQL-Bridge, users of SQL databases can search across bothstructured and unstructured data.andP;  The capabilities of Topic itself have beenextended to include complex query and analysis of structured data as well asreport generation.andM;In another move to support graphics and user-interface standards, theofficials said they hope to offer support for X windows by the end of theyear.andM;Topic version 2.0 is completing beta test now and will be shipped next month.andO;Topic software for clients is priced at $2,500 for workstations.andP;  Prices forusual configurations, which include Topic Database Builder, Topic DatabaseServer and Retrieval Clients, range from $7,500 to $110,000.andP;  Topic Real-Timeis $15,000, and the Topic SQL-Bridge is $2,500.andM;For additional information, Verity Inc. can be contacted at 1550 PlymouthSt., Mountain Vew, CA 94043-1230, (415) 960-7600.andO;</TEXT></DOC>